Indeed, you are right. Option 1 is not appealing for my implementation. As for option 2, I am displaying the dialoghost in a View Model using the following code:

var addNewView = new AddNewView(RecId, RecNo);
await DialogHost.Show(addNewView, "RootDialog");

In this case, I am facing another challenge to search the Handle from WindowsFormsHost.Child in the Visual Tree. Do you know how can I do it? I am struggling to create a DependencyObject for WindowsFormsHost which will have a method to get PictureBox.Handle.

Let me know. Thanks.

