Hi guys,

I have an application with a lot of controls and I've implemented a method for change the primary color of the software as follows:

    private string _theme = "blue";
    public string Theme
    {
        get { return _theme; }
        set
        {
            _theme = value.ToLower();
            OnPropertyChanged();
            var theme = Themes.FirstOrDefault(c => c.Name == _theme);
            new PaletteHelper().ReplacePrimaryColor(theme);
        }
    }


Essentially each time this property is called, the method `ReplacePrimaryColor` is firing, but this method freeze the app for 1-2 seconds delay (depend on the pc). Is there a way to avoid that situation?

Kind regards.

